#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:0
msgid "# CV 融合算子开发"
msgstr "# CV Fusion Operator Development"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:2
msgid "CV 融合算子指同一个算子中同时使用 Cube Core 和 Vector Core：Cube Core 通常负责 `tl.dot`、矩阵乘或卷积式主计算，Vector Core 负责 bias、activation、softmax、归约、mask、layout 重排或跨块同步。CV 融合的目标是减少 kernel 边界和 GM 往返，但需要同时控制 Cube tile、Vector tile、UB/L1 占用和同步关系。"
msgstr "CV fusion operator refers to an operator that simultaneously uses Cube Core and Vector Core within the same operator: Cube Core is typically responsible for `tl.dot`, matrix multiplication, or convolution-like main computations, while Vector Core handles bias, activation, softmax, reduction, mask, layout rearrangement, or cross-block synchronization. The goal of CV fusion is to reduce kernel boundaries and GM round trips, but it requires simultaneous control over Cube tile, Vector tile, UB/L1 occupancy, and synchronization relationships."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:4
msgid "## CV 融合简单算子开发"
msgstr "## CV Fusion Simple Operator Development"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:6
msgid "简单 CV 融合建议先从本仓 [矩阵乘法样例](../examples/05_matrix_multiplication_example.md) 抽出稳定的 `tl.dot` 主计算，再在写回前加入 Vector 后处理；更复杂的切片更新可参考 [融合注意力样例](../examples/04_fused_attention_example.md)。最小路径如下："
msgstr "For simple CV fusion, it is recommended to first extract the stable `tl.dot` main computation from the [matrix multiplication example](../examples/05_matrix_multiplication_example.md) in this repository, and then add Vector post-processing before writing back. For more complex slice updates, refer to the [fused attention example](../examples/04_fused_attention_example.md). The minimal path is as follows:"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:8
msgid ""
"1. 先实现稳定的 Cube 主计算，例如 `acc = tl.dot(a, b, acc)`。\n"
"2. 在 accumulator 写回前融合轻量 Vector 后处理，例如 bias、scale、activation 或 dtype cast。\n"
"3. 对较大的 accumulator，可使用 `range` 配合 `extension.extract_slice`/`extension.insert_slice` 做普通子块切分，避免 Vector 后处理阶段 UB overflow。\n"
"4. `extension.parallel(..., bind_sub_block=True)` 属于更强的显式多 Vector 子块绑定路径，目标硬件和编译配置存在差异时可能不可用，不建议作为简单示例的默认写法。\n"
msgstr ""
"1. First implement a stable Cube main computation, e.g., `acc = tl.dot(a, b, acc)`.\n"
"2. Fuse lightweight Vector post-processing before writing back the accumulator, e.g., bias, scale, activation, or dtype cast.\n"
"3. For larger accumulators, use `range` with `extension.extract_slice`/`extension.insert_slice` to perform ordinary sub-block partitioning, avoiding UB overflow in the Vector post-processing stage.\n"
"4. `extension.parallel(..., bind_sub_block=True)` is a stronger explicit multi-Vector sub-block binding path, which may be unavailable when target hardware and compilation configurations differ; it is not recommended as the default approach for simple examples.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:10
msgid "示例结构："
msgstr "Example structure:"

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:12
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"# 在 matmul kernel 内部，K 循环完成后得到 fp32 accumulator。\n"
"acc = tl.dot(a, b, acc)  # 通常位于 K 维循环内，这里仅展示结构。\n"
"\n"
"# 在写回前融合轻量 Vector 后处理。\n"
"acc = tl.where(acc >= 0, acc, 0.01 * acc)\n"
"c = acc.to(tl.float16)\n"
"\n"
"offs_m = pid_m * BLOCK_M + tl.arange(0, BLOCK_M)\n"
"offs_n = pid_n * BLOCK_N + tl.arange(0, BLOCK_N)\n"
"c_ptrs = c_ptr + offs_m[:, None] * stride_cm + offs_n[None, :] * stride_cn\n"
"c_mask = (offs_m[:, None] < M) & (offs_n[None, :] < N)\n"
"tl.store(c_ptrs, c, mask=c_mask)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:14
msgid "简单 CV 融合开发时要保持边界清晰：Cube 负责产生较大的二维 accumulator，Vector 负责同一 tile 内的逐元素或小规模归约。若 Vector 部分需要跨多个 Cube tile 共享状态，就需要引入同步、workspace 或拆分 kernel。"
msgstr "When developing simple CV fusion, keep boundaries clear: Cube is responsible for generating larger two-dimensional accumulators, while Vector handles element-wise or small-scale reductions within the same tile. If the Vector part needs to share state across multiple Cube tiles, synchronization, workspace, or kernel splitting must be introduced."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:16
msgid "## CV 融合复杂算子开发"
msgstr "## CV Fusion Complex Operator Development"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:18
msgid "复杂 CV 融合可参考 [Ascend/triton-ascend-ops](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops) 中的 best practice："
msgstr "For complex CV fusion, refer to the best practice in [Ascend/triton-ascend-ops](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops)."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:20
msgid ""
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/002-decode_grouped_attention.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/002-decode_grouped_attention.py)：Decode attention 中 QK/PV 使用 Cube，softmax、mask、指数、归一化和离散 KV 访存重排使用 Vector。\n"
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/003-fused-cat-slice-conv1d.zh.md`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/003-fused-cat-slice-conv1d.zh.md)：展示融合 cat、slice、conv1d update 时如何用 `extension.insert_slice`、转置和分核优化减少离散访存与 padding 开销。\n"
msgstr ""
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/002-decode_grouped_attention.py`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/002-decode_grouped_attention.py): In Decode attention, QK/PV uses Cube, while softmax, mask, exponent, normalization, and discrete KV memory access rearrangement use Vector.\n"
"- [`tutorial/best_practice/003-fused-cat-slice-conv1d.zh.md`](https://github.com/Ascend/triton-ascend-ops/blob/main/tutorial/best_practice/003-fused-cat-slice-conv1d.zh.md): Demonstrates how to use `extension.insert_slice`, transpose, and kernel splitting optimization to reduce discrete memory access and padding overhead when fusing cat, slice, and conv1d update.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:22
msgid "复杂 CV 融合建议按数据流分层组织："
msgstr "For complex CV fusion, it is recommended to organize by data flow layers."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:24
msgid ""
"1. **主计算层**：识别哪些步骤必须走 Cube，例如 QK、PV、GEMM、batched matmul。\n"
"2. **Vector 后处理层**：识别 softmax、activation、mask、scale、normalization、cat/slice、layout transform 等是否能在同一 tile 内完成。\n"
"3. **访存重排层**：对离散 KV cache、MoE token 重排、短尾轴 tensor，优先在 UB 中用 `extension.insert_slice`、`extension.extract_slice`、转置或借轴转置形成硬件友好的连续访问。\n"
"4. **流水和同步层**：通过 `multibuffer`、`set_workspace_multibuffer`、`tile_mix_vector_loop`、`tile_mix_cube_loop` 等编译选项探索 Cube 与 Vector 的重叠执行。\n"
"5. **分核层**：CV 融合算子通常按 Cube Core 数量发射 grid；运行时会以约 1:2 的比例协同 Vector Core。不要简单沿用 GPU 上的大 grid。\n"
msgstr ""
"1. **Main Compute Layer**: Identifies which steps must go through Cube, such as QK, PV, GEMM, and batched matmul.\n"
"2. **Vector Post-Processing Layer**: Determines whether operations like softmax, activation, mask, scale, normalization, cat/slice, and layout transform can be completed within the same tile.\n"
"3. **Memory Access Reordering Layer**: For discrete KV cache, MoE token reordering, and short-tail axis tensors, prioritize using `extension.insert_slice`, `extension.extract_slice`, transpose, or axis borrowing transpose in UB to form hardware-friendly contiguous access.\n"
"4. **Pipeline and Synchronization Layer**: Explores overlapping execution of Cube and Vector through compilation options such as `multibuffer`, `set_workspace_multibuffer`, `tile_mix_vector_loop`, and `tile_mix_cube_loop`.\n"
"5. **Kernel Distribution Layer**: CV fusion operators typically launch grids based on the number of Cube cores; at runtime, Vector cores are coordinated at approximately a 1:2 ratio. Do not simply follow the large grid approach used on GPUs.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:26
msgid "对于 attention 类 CV 融合，推荐先让非 causal、短序列、小 head_dim 的 case 跑通，再逐步加入："
msgstr "For attention-based CV fusion, it is recommended to first get the non-causal, short sequence, small head_dim cases working, then gradually add:"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:28
msgid ""
"- causal mask 分阶段处理。\n"
"- 长序列 K/V block 循环。\n"
"- `m_i`/`l_i` 的数值稳定 softmax 更新。\n"
"- HEAD_DIM 较大时的 accumulator workspace 和子块切分。\n"
"- KV cache 离散索引下的 load 重排。\n"
msgstr ""
"- Causal mask processing in stages.\n"
"- Long sequence K/V block looping.\n"
"- Numerically stable softmax update for `m_i`/`l_i`.\n"
"- Accumulator workspace and sub-block partitioning when HEAD_DIM is large.\n"
"- Load reordering under discrete indexing of KV cache.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/programming_guide/cv_fusion_operator.md:30
msgid "复杂 CV 融合调优时，优先观察 profiling 中 Cube、Vector、MTE2 的时间占比。如果 Cube 等待 Vector，考虑减少 Vector 后处理粒度或打开 CV balance 相关选项；如果 Vector 等待搬运，优先检查离散访存、tail-axis padding 和 multibuffer 配置。"
msgstr "When tuning complex CV fusion, first observe the time proportions of Cube, Vector, and MTE2 in profiling. If Cube is waiting for Vector, consider reducing the granularity of Vector post-processing or enabling CV balance-related options; if Vector is waiting for data movement, prioritize checking discrete memory access, tail-axis padding, and multibuffer configuration."

